oECAsQRA#v=onepage&q=isolde%20standish%20oshima%20nagisa&f=false|title=Politics, Porn and Protest: Japanese Avant-Garde Cinema in the 1960s and 1970s|date=2011-06-02|publisher=A&C Black|isbn=978-0-8264-3901-7|language=en}}</ref>\n** Standish, Isolde (2007) 'Transgression and the Politics of Porn. Oshima Nagisa's In the Realm of the Senses (1976)'. In: Phillips, A. and Stringer, J., (eds.), ''Japanese Cinema: Texts and Contexts''. Abingdon: Routledge, pp 217-228).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tufs.ac.jp/research/js/interview/2019/05/post-50.html|title=\u30a4\u30be\u30eb\u30c0\u30fb\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5|website=\u6559\u54e1\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc|language=ja|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n==Writings==\n\n*''Pasolini Renaissance'', {{ISBN|978-4925095044}}\n\n===Translations===\n*\"Ai ga Fukamaru Hon - \"Honto no Yorokobi\" o shiru tame ni\" (translation of \"Making Heart-to-Heart Love in Bed\" by John Gray) {{ISBN|978-4837970170}}\n*\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30fb\u30d1\u30fc\u30c8\u30ca\u30fc\u306b\u306a\u308b\u305f\u3081\u306b\u2015\u7537\u3068\u5973\u304c\u77e5\u3063\u3066\u304a\u304f\u3079\u304d\u300c\u5206\u304b\u3061\u611b\u300d\u306e\u30eb\u30fc\u30eb \u7537\u306f\u706b\u661f\u304b\u3089\u3001\u5973\u306f\u91d1\u661f\u304b\u3089\u3084\u3063\u3066\u304d\u305f (translation of \"[[Men Are from Mars, Women Are from Venus]]\" by John Gray) {{ISBN|978-4837971764}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n===References===\n*{{turim-oshima}}\n*{{audie-bock-directors}}\n*{{cite book|last=Oshima|first=Nagisa|title=Cinema, Censorship And The State|publisher=MIT Press|year=1992|location=Cambridge|ref=harv|isbn=0-262-65039-8}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.oshima-pro.jp/ OSHIMA PRODUCTIONS LTD]\n*{{IMDb name|0651915}}\n* [http://www.japan-zone.com/modern/oshima_nagisa.shtml Profile] at Japan Zone\n* {{cite journal |url= http://www.sensesofcinema.com/2004/great-directors/oshima/ |journal= Senses of Cinema |title= Profile |series= Great Direc